        public boolean shouldLogOnNullSet(java.lang.String arg0,
                         java.lang.String arg1)
        Description copied from interface: org.apache.velocity.app.event.NullSetEventHandler
        Called when the RHS of a #set() is null, which will result in a null LHS. All NullSetEventHandlers are called in sequence until a false is returned. If no NullSetEventHandler is registered all nulls will be logged.
        Specified by:
        shouldLogOnNullSet in interface org.apache.velocity.app.event.NullSetEventHandler
        Parameters:
        arg0 - reference literal of left-hand-side of set statement
        arg1 - reference literal of right-hand-side of set statement
        Returns:
        true if log message should be written, false otherwise
